FRANCE DAYBOOK: EU Finance Minister Talk of Greek Debt Schedule

-- B y  
-- 
2011-05-18T04:06:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/france-daybook-eu-finance-minister-talk-of-greek-debt-schedule.html
European finance ministers for the
first time floated the idea of talks with bondholders over
extending  Greece ’s debt-repayment schedule, saying that last
year’s 110 billion-euro ($156 billion) rescue has failed to
restore the country to financial health.  ALL TIMES CET  WHAT TO WATCH:
* French President’s briefing to journalists on May 26-26 Group
of Eight meeting  EARNINGS:
- Areva SA (CEI)   said it had completed the exchange offer for
investment certificates into ordinary shares.  -Unibail-Rodamco (UL FP) must pay 87.66 euros plus interest for
each of the 660,562 Rodamco Europe NV shares it doesn’t already
own, the Amsterdam Court of Appeal ruled.  ECONOMY:
* Ramon Fernandez, head of Treasury, speaks to lawmakers about
the competitiveness of the French economy. 4 pm.  GOVERNMENT:
* Cabinet Meeting. 10:00 a.m.
* French Industry Minister Eric Besson speech to fashion
industry group 12 p.m
* French President Sarkozy meets Tunisian Prime Minister
Essebsi. 1 p.m.
* French President’s briefing to journalists on May 26-26 Group
of Eight meeting  EQUITIES:
* 10:30 a.m. Credit Agricole SA holds its annual shareholders
meeting in Strasbourg.  MARKETS:
*The CAC 40 Index fell 48.24, or 1.2 percent, to 3,941.58.
*The broader SBF 120 Index fell 1.2 percent.  INTERVIEWS ELSEWHERE:
